

Keywords:
		Search keywords: 	SV VMM vmm_channel Transaction Level Interfaces 
 
Technical content:
 
		Title:   Setting up and using Transaction level interfaces using vmm_channel  	
 
		Objective: 	Demonstrate the usage of the vmm_channel class and its asscoiated methods to implement transactionlevel interfaces and to exchange transactions through blocking/non blocking methods across mulitple TL threads 
		Description: 	
		The different channel APIs like : put/get/sneak/activate/flush/reconfigure/level are used to show their behaviour

		Additional setup: None	
 
 To run the example:
      Using Makefile:
       	clean           -- To clean up the log files and executable of previous run
       	comp            -- To compile the design
        run             -- To run the design
        all             -- It does all the above steps.
     Using shell scripts:
        clean.csh       -- To clean up the log files and executable of previous run
        comp.csh        -- To compile the design
        run.csh         -- To run the design  
 
 
Location Information:
		PATH: 			$VCS_HOME/doc/examples/testbench/sv/vmm/std_lib/vmm_channel/channel_basic
